Now, the fixed code: We need to modify the isCachable method to include checks for _anySetter, _propertyBasedCreator, _valueInstantiator. Also maybe _delegateDeserializer, etc. But the standard fix from Jackson is:

```
public boolean isCachable() {
    return (_valueTypeDeserializer == null)
            && (_ignorableProperties == null)
            && (_anySetter == null)
            && (_propertyBasedCreator == null)
            && (_valueInstantiator == null || _valueInstantiator.canCreateUsingDefault());
}
```

Note: Also check for _delegateDeserializer? In later versions, they also check _delegateDeserializer, but for the given issue, the added checks are _anySetter, _propertyBasedCreator, _valueInstantiator.

